<subSubSection id="459D7EBDFFFEFFE2FF3CFDE84EFB65CD" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFFEFFE2FF3CFDE84F2E655E" blockId="12.[151,618,578,604]" box="[151,618,578,604]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading id="56709A5AFFFEFFE2FF3CFDE84F2E655E" bold="true" box="[151,618,578,604]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FF3CFDE84F2E655E" bold="true" box="[151,618,578,604]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FF3CFDE84CFE655E" authorityName="Lutken, 1892 Pseudoscopelus scriptus Lutken" authorityYear="1892" box="[151,442,578,604]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FF3CFDE84CFE655E" bold="true" box="[151,442,578,604]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pseudoscopelus scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFFEFFE2FF3CFD274EFB65CD" blockId="12.[151,1440,653,1999]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FF3CFD274C7A65A5" bold="true" box="[151,318,653,679]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Composition.</emphasis>
The 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FED2FD274FDC65A4" authorityName="Lutken, 1892 Pseudoscopelus scriptus Lutken" authorityYear="1892" box="[377,664,653,678]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FED2FD274FDC65A4" box="[377,664,653,678]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pseudoscopelus scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group is composed of six species: 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FB23FD27484865A4" authorityName="Fowler, 1934 Pseudoscopelus cephalus Fowler" authorityYear="1934" box="[1160,1292,653,678]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cephalus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FB23FD27484865A4" box="[1160,1292,653,678]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. cephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FAB1FD274DB065CC" authorityName="Melo, 2010 Pseudoscopelus cordilluminatus Melo" authorityYear="2010" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cordilluminatus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FAB1FD274DB065CC" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. cordilluminatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FEA9FD1F4CE665CC" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1934" box="[258,418,693,718]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusifrons">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FEA9FD1F4CE665CC" box="[258,418,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. obtusifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FE1BFD1F4F0365CC" box="[432,583,693,718]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pierbartus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FE1BFD1F4F0365CC" box="[432,583,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. pierbartus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FDFDFD1F4FBA65CC" authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1908" box="[598,766,693,718]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sagamianus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FDFDFD1F4FBA65CC" box="[598,766,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. sagamianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FC94FD1F4EFC65CC" authorityName="Lutken, 1892 Pseudoscopelus scriptus Lutken" authorityYear="1892" box="[831,952,693,718]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FC94FD1F4EFC65CC" box="[831,952,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="459D7EBDFFFEFFE3FF6DFD7749EE6678" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFFEFFE2FF6DFD7749E76225" blockId="12.[151,1440,653,1999]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FF6DFD774C0265F5" bold="true" box="[198,326,733,759]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FE29FD774FE665F4" authorityName="Lutken, 1892 Pseudoscopelus scriptus Lutken" authorityYear="1892" box="[386,674,733,758]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FE29FD774FE665F4" box="[386,674,733,758]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pseudoscopelus scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group is diagnosed from its congeners by unique configuration of supraorbital canal pores and photophore pattern: supraorbital canal pores modally five, small pore of supraorbital canal, medial to supranasal pore usually absent, with the exception of the 
<typeStatus id="D23C9394FFFEFFE2FAA5FC8748316445" box="[1294,1397,813,839]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FF3CFCFF4C5B646C" authorityName="Fowler, 1934 Pseudoscopelus cephalus Fowler" authorityYear="1934" box="[151,287,853,878]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cephalus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FF3CFCFF4C5B646C" box="[151,287,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. cephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a few specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FDFDFCFF4E6A646C" authorityName="Melo, 2010 Pseudoscopelus cordilluminatus Melo" authorityYear="2010" box="[598,814,853,878]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cordilluminatus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FDFDFCFF4E6A646C" box="[598,814,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. cordilluminatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FCE8FCFF4E27646C" box="[835,867,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs.</emphasis>
supraorbital canal pores six, the small pore of supraorbital medial to supranasal pore always present in all other species of 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FBA5FCD7498D6494" box="[1038,1225,893,918]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FBA5FCD7498D6494" box="[1038,1225,893,918]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pseudoscopelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); luminescent tissue present as discrete photophores (
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FDEDFC0F4F2164BC" box="[582,613,933,958]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs.</emphasis>
completely absent in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FCCCFC0F4E8E64BC" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev, 2005 Pseudoscopelus aphos Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2005" box="[871,970,933,958]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aphos">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FCCCFC0F4E8E64BC" box="[871,970,933,958]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. aphos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and represented as vestigial white lines in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FF1EFC674C5D64E4" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev, 2006 Pseudoscopelus parini Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[181,281,973,998]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parini">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FF1EFC674C5D64E4" box="[181,281,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. parini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FE99FC674C1864E4" box="[306,348,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">mxf</emphasis>
arranged in an elongate continuous row that extends from level of posterior margin of eye to the angle between preopercle and dentary, and 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FD11FC5F4FA4630C" box="[698,736,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">apf</emphasis>
absent (
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FCE9FC5F4ED7630C" box="[834,915,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs. mxf</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FC60FC5F4EB5630C" box="[971,1009,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">apf</emphasis>
absent in the species of the 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FA93FC5F4DFD6334" authorityName="Krefft, 1971 Pseudoscopelus scutatus Krefft" authorityYear="1971" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scutatus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FA93FC5F4DFD6334" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P.scutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group; 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FEDEFBB74CDB6334" box="[373,415,1053,1078]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">mxf</emphasis>
absent and 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FD84FBB74F106334" box="[559,596,1053,1078]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">apf</emphasis>
present in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FD71FBB74E316334" box="[730,885,1053,1078]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lavenbergi">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FD71FBB74E316334" box="[730,885,1053,1078]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. lavenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FC2DFBB74EF46334" box="[902,944,1053,1078]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">mxf</emphasis>
short, not connected posteriorly with 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FADDFBB748D86334" box="[1398,1436,1053,1078]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">apf</emphasis>
present in the 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FE96FBEF4F56635C" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev, 2006 Pseudoscopelus astronesthidens Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[317,530,1093,1118]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="astronesthidens">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FE96FBEF4F56635C" box="[317,530,1093,1118]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. astronesthidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group; and 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FD57FBEF4E62635C" box="[764,806,1093,1118]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">mxf</emphasis>
irregular, with widely spaced photophores anteriorly, and connected with 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FE2CFBC74CE86384" box="[391,428,1133,1158]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">apf</emphasis>
posteriorly in the 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FD20FBC74E5C6384" authorityName="Parr, 1933 Pseudoscopelus altipinnis Parr" authorityYear="1933" box="[651,792,1133,1158]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="altipinnis">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FD20FBC74E5C6384" box="[651,792,1133,1158]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. altipinnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group); 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FC75FBC74EAA6384" box="[990,1006,1133,1158]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">if</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FB80FBC7491E6384" box="[1067,1114,1133,1158]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">prvf</emphasis>
continuous (
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FB5CFBC748746384" box="[1271,1328,1133,1158]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs. if</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FAC7FBC748D86384" box="[1388,1436,1133,1158]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">prvf</emphasis>
disconnected at level of cleithrum in all other species of 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FC82FB3F4EA063AC" box="[809,996,1173,1198]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FC82FB3F4EA063AC" box="[809,996,1173,1198]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pseudoscopelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FC56FB3F495D63AC" box="[1021,1049,1173,1198]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">trf</emphasis>
in a single row of closely spaced photophores, with a medial, circular cluster (
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FD1EFB174FBF63D4" box="[693,763,1213,1238]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs. trf</emphasis>
absent in the 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FC02FB17493B63D4" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev, 2006 Pseudoscopelus astronesthidens Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[937,1151,1213,1238]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="astronesthidens">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FC02FB17493B63D4" box="[937,1151,1213,1238]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. astronesthidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FB16FB17487963D4" authorityName="Krefft, 1971 Pseudoscopelus scutatus Krefft" authorityYear="1971" box="[1213,1341,1213,1238]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scutatus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FB16FB17487963D4" box="[1213,1341,1213,1238]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. scutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species groups; 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FF52FB4F4C5163FC" box="[249,277,1253,1278]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">trf</emphasis>
arranged in a broad band of three or four photophores in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FC75FB4F493E63FC" box="[990,1146,1253,1278]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lavenbergi">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FC75FB4F493E63FC" box="[990,1146,1253,1278]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. lavenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and in a single row of widely spaced photophores without the medial cluster in the 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FCF4FAA74EAE6224" authorityName="Parr, 1933 Pseudoscopelus altipinnis Parr" authorityYear="1933" box="[863,1002,1293,1318]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="altipinnis">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FCF4FAA74EAE6224" box="[863,1002,1293,1318]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. altipinnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFFEFFE2FF6DFA9F4C0462ED" blockId="12.[151,1440,653,1999]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FF6DFA9F4E32624D" bold="true" box="[198,886,1333,1359]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ontogenetic changes and the identification of juveniles.</emphasis>
Characteristics of dentition are of great importance to diagnose the species of the 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FD96FAF74E196274" authorityName="Lutken, 1892 Pseudoscopelus scriptus Lutken" authorityYear="1892" box="[573,861,1373,1398]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FD96FAF74E196274" box="[573,861,1373,1398]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pseudoscopelus scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group; however, they are not completely developed in specimens less than 45.0 mm, with the exception of 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FC36FA2F497A629C" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1934" box="[925,1086,1413,1438]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusifrons">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FC36FA2F497A629C" box="[925,1086,1413,1438]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. obtusifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Ontogenetic changes in dentition are best understood in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FE41FA074F2162C4" authorityName="Lutken, 1892 Pseudoscopelus scriptus Lutken" authorityYear="1892" box="[490,613,1453,1478]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FE41FA074F2162C4" box="[490,613,1453,1478]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because it is very well represented in scientific collections in a wide range of sizes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFFEFFE3FF6DFA574CE46600" blockId="12.[151,1440,653,1999]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,152,378]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Juveniles of 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FEF4FA574FC56114" authorityName="Lutken, 1892 Pseudoscopelus scriptus Lutken" authorityYear="1892" box="[351,641,1533,1558]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FEF4FA574FC56114" box="[351,641,1533,1558]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pseudoscopelus scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have teeth arranged similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FC51FA5749D76114" box="[1018,1171,1533,1558]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pierbartus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FC51FA5749D76114" box="[1018,1171,1533,1558]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. pierbartus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the premaxilla is not very wide (10–12% in length) and dentition arranged in three series of a single row of teeth each, with the mesial series having few teeth. Because the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FCEDF9E74E846164" authorityName="Lutken, 1892 Pseudoscopelus scriptus Lutken" authorityYear="1892" box="[838,960,1613,1638]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FCEDF9E74E846164" box="[838,960,1613,1638]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FC53F9E749CA6164" box="[1016,1166,1613,1638]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pierbartus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FC53F9E749CA6164" box="[1016,1166,1613,1638]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. pierbartus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
overlaps, the juveniles cannot be separated easily, but in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FD86F9DF4F82618C" box="[557,710,1653,1678]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pierbartus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FD86F9DF4F82618C" box="[557,710,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. pierbartus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FD57F9DF4E5A618C" box="[764,798,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">saf</emphasis>
extends a little more anteriorly, reaching the level of anus, than in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FE96F9374CFD61B4" authorityName="Lutken, 1892 Pseudoscopelus scriptus Lutken" authorityYear="1892" box="[317,441,1693,1718]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FE96F9374CFD61B4" box="[317,441,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This allows making tentative identifications. The number of rows of teeth in the mesial series of the premaxilla increases with size, starting in specimens of about 31.0–32.0 mm SL and reaching full development by 45.0 mm SL. Teeth of the mesial row in a specimen of 31.0 mm SL (
<accessionNumber id="12D4B0D5FFFEFFE2FAF1F9474DA6602D" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/MCZ68463" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">MCZ 68463</accessionNumber>
) are externally developed, but are not attached to the bone; in a 
<quantity id="CA7F80D3FFFEFFE2FC7BF8BF497D602D" box="[976,1081,1813,1839]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.18" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="31.8">31.8 mm</quantity>
SL specimen (UF 19987), the teeth of the left side of the premaxilla has the adult arrangement and are completely attached to bone, but in the left side it is as juvenile. A 
<quantity id="CA7F80D3FFFEFFE2FDA9F8CF4F2F607D" box="[514,619,1893,1919]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.45" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="44.5">44.5 mm</quantity>
SL specimen (MCZ 101790) is the smallest specimen examined with fully developed dentition on the premaxilla and dentary. 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FC9FF827492460A4" authorityName="Fowler, 1934 Pseudoscopelus cephalus Fowler" authorityYear="1934" box="[820,1120,1933,1958]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cephalus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FC9FF827492460A4" box="[820,1120,1933,1958]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pseudoscopelus cephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FBC4F827480060A4" authorityName="Melo, 2010 Pseudoscopelus cordilluminatus Melo" authorityYear="2010" box="[1135,1348,1933,1958]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cordilluminatus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FBC4F827480060A4" box="[1135,1348,1933,1958]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. cordilluminatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFEFFE2FA2DF8274C6760CC" authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1908" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sagamianus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFEFFE2FA2DF8274C6760CC" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. sagamianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not common in scientific collections and a good series of juveniles is not available. A 
<quantity id="CA7F80D3FFFEFFE3FAC2F81F4D8167B0" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.44" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="24.4">24.4 mm</quantity>
SL specimen (USNM 200533), tentatively identified as 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFFFFE3FCF1FF32496A67B3" authorityName="Melo, 2010 Pseudoscopelus cordilluminatus Melo" authorityYear="2010" box="[858,1070,152,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cordilluminatus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFFFFE3FCF1FF32496A67B3" box="[858,1070,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. cordilluminatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has some growing teeth under the skin. In 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFFFFE3FE8FFF6A4C8167DB" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1934" box="[292,453,192,217]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusifrons">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFFFFE3FE8FFF6A4C8167DB" box="[292,453,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. obtusifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the diagnostic hooked teeth flared outwards are developed in a 
<quantity id="CA7F80D3FFFFFFE3FB11FF6A486767D8" box="[1210,1315,192,218]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.68" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="16.8">16.8 mm</quantity>
SL specimen (USNM 200535).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFFFFFE3FF6DFEBA49EE6678" blockId="13.[151,1436,152,378]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFFFFE3FF6DFEBA4CA2662B" authorityName="Lutken, 1892 Pseudoscopelus scriptus Lutken" authorityYear="1892" box="[198,486,272,297]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFFFFE3FF6DFEBA4CA2662B" box="[198,486,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Pseudoscopelus scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFFFFE3FDB5FEBA4FFA662B" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1934" box="[542,702,272,297]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusifrons">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFFFFE3FDB5FEBA4FFA662B" box="[542,702,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. obtusifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have allometric, statistically significant growth of the pectoral fin: in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFFFFE3FF4EFE924C1B6653" authorityName="Lutken, 1892 Pseudoscopelus scriptus Lutken" authorityYear="1892" box="[229,351,312,337]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFFFFE3FF4EFE924C1B6653" box="[229,351,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the growth is positive (p=0.001); in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFFFFFE3FCA6FE924EE96653" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1934" box="[781,941,312,337]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusifrons">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFFFFFE3FCA6FE924EE96653" box="[781,941,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. obtusifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is negative (p=0.042); this explains the large standard deviation variation found for both species (SD= 5.3 and 3.2, respectively).
</paragraph>
